Part II.: Conditions for obtaining and maintaining the authorisation of an authorised investment fund manager (IFM) who engages solely in the activity of management of UCIs as laid down in Article 101(2) of the 2010 Law and Article 5(2) of the 2013 Law > Chapter 6.: Bodies of IFM > Sub-chapter 6.3: Bodies of IFM > Sub-section 6.3.2.1: Required Number

The senior management must maintain a contractual relationship with the institution. This ensures proper governance and accountability structures are in place.

original_block.text: The senior management must maintain a contractual relationship with the institution. This ensures proper governance and accountability structures are in place.

content:
Part II.: Conditions for obtaining and maintaining the authorisation of an authorised investment fund manager (IFM) who engages solely in the activity of management of UCIs as laid down in Article 101(2) of the 2010 Law and Article 5(2) of the 2013 Law > Chapter 6.: Bodies of IFM > Sub-chapter 6.3: Bodies of IFM > Section 6: Required Number

The minimum number of senior management members required is three, with at least one having expertise in financial management.

original_block.text: The minimum number of senior management members required is three, with at least one having expertise in financial management.

content:
Part I.: Definitions and abbreviations

Investment Fund Manager (IFM): An entity that manages investment funds and is subject to regulatory oversight.
